76561198104040378,Recommended,314240,23605098,"Posted: 16 June, 2016",all,Pneumo,"If the words 'rpg' or 'tycoon' spark your attention, buy this game.Being one of those that sat for many hours playing hospital tycoon/ theme park/ rollercoaster tycoon/ zoo tycoon etc etc- this game sparked my attention. so i bought it. i didnt play it much at first but recently it updated and i started playing again.Its much like 'Game Dev tycoon' with building aspects, quests to do (epic quests have loot drops), team and captured town  management and a dice roll/ text parts of the quests undertaken. Quests give experience, both toward the heros that youve sent out, and your kingdom, that goes toward new building types, kingdom expansion and player stats, that affect your dice roll during quests.The gameplay is verymuch sandbox, but you can choose to undertake the general progression type quests, that give you money when youve completed a small list, which leads to another list, with more money.You can also start a custom game, where you can choose how much starting money you have, experience amounts given, etc etc...The devs are also happy to let people mod the game, and apparently its easily done... and, you can (if not a mod maker/coding expert like myself,) you have to ability to write your own quest stories and layout (not that ive done so, but still.) ...I've checked therough the files saved on the compueter however, and i can see that, the config files are also quite easily changed... so theres that too.EDIT: I have recently been in contact with a developer of this game, and they seemed very considerate and detailed within their responses. Good news.....Yes, there have been issues with bugs, but upon realising that after uninstalling the game, files were left behind, so i deleted them after searching 'my computer' and then using Ccleaner to scan and delete old files and registry files3- i re installed and the game is prettymuch working perfectly, dont be offput by negative reviews... its a one /two man team thatve been working on the game for a few years, and, through reading the replies from the devs toward bug reporting comments- the dev/s understand there are issues, and havent made any poor comments toward constructive criticism.be patient...it'll be worth it, im sure.I've rebuilt and started over too many times... its my own fault, i cant help it."
