76561198061032562,Recommended,314240,16133538,"Posted: 2 June, 2015",all,Count_Joshoo,"Like many other reviews I give this thumbs up for potential.  The game still needs a ton of work and fine tuning and, frankly, content.On the PROS side is the basic concept.  Run a village as AI Heroes do all the adventuring.  I have no doubt the finished product will be a good game and worth the money, but I'm holding out hope that it will be a great game that is a steal for the price.On the CONS side there is a quite a bit wrong or off.  The FTL lite ""Epic Quests"" feel like random 50/50 guesses.  When it asked me to help a farmer with his pigs 4 times in 4 straight quests I said ""yes"" all four times.  Wrong each time.  However I have no idea how this matters other than XP not gained.  This transitions nicely into the overall lack of a feeling that my decisions matter other than keeping the town in net gains money wise.  2 hours into the game and I don't even read the quest bits anymore, I just pick and option at random and roll on.  100+ hours in FTL and I still read the text.The notifications are also super annoying, they constantly pop up to tell me that it is autosaving, which by the way is frequent and necessary, and to tell me a quest is done.  Of course the quest is done, I just navigated a bunch of pop ups telling me the same information.  Again, we are dealing with information that quickly becomes superflous, which is not a great trait for a resource management game to have.The bonus giving objective queue seems to run out after about 4 sets, though if I remember correctly the Dev noted that is going to be a big part of the next update.I know I mostly have complaints/critiques here, and I could probably find more.  So why recommended still? Because I really really want this game to be great, it's my first alpha build purchase and I want other people to try it out and offer even smarter feedback than I can.Thanks for what you are doing Dev, for the large amount of resource management games out there the lack of quality and non-Farmville variety is sad.  Keep working hard and making this game everything it can grow to be!"
