,Recommended,314240,23188902,"Posted: 24 May, 2016",all,LetTheRaineFall,"I have such a love-hate relatoinship with this game right now. I'll start with the bad.Yes people have said bugs, but what bugs? Let me mention my two most annoying ones.1. Deleted/messed up save files. I'll go back in to play and I will be pushed back by a lot of progress and I'll forget how I got to where I'd been so I just start over which is really annoying after the 5th time. The most recent occurence could have been because the game updated, not sure.2. I would click on a character and click on their name and a box would come up, but I couldn't get rid of it and I would have to close out of the game and lose my progress.In addition to this it does bother me a bit that the difficulty curve on epic quests is a bit odd but whatever.Now on to the good!I first purchased this game I think last year? Not sure exactly. But a ton of things have been improved since then making things more logical, giving more options, and I love all of the equipment and items. Really it's becoming a thorough game.I think that this game has a ton of potential but it's still not perfect. I really suggest that anyone try this out, especially those who like time management, rpg mechanics, tycoon games (obviously), or anyone with some free time on their hands. The price is worth it."
